  <static seed="1401" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/addSubtractRationalExpressions90.pg">
    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{x}{x-4}-\frac{x+12}{x^{2}-4x}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{x+3}{x}, x\ne 4</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{x}{x-4}-\frac{x+12}{x^{2}-4x}} 
      \amp = {\frac{x}{x-4}}-\frac{{x+12}}{x(x - 4)} \\
      \amp = \frac{x \cdot x}{({x-4}) \cdot x}-\frac{{x+12}}{x(x - 4)} \\
      \amp = \frac{x^{2}}{x(x - 4)}-\frac{{x+12}}{x(x - 4)} \\
      \amp = \frac{x^{2}-({x+12})}{x(x - 4)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{x^{2}-x-12}}{x(x - 4)} \\
      \amp = \frac{(x - 4)(x+3)}{x(x - 4)} \\
      \amp = {\frac{x+3}{x}, x\ne 4}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>{x-4}</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>x \ne {4}</m>.</p>
</solution>
